message.content:
Before Cam broke his arm, he typed at a rate of 9 words per minute. In 5 minutes, he would be able to type:

9 words/minute * 5 minutes = 45 words

After he broke his arm and had to use his left hand, he could only type at a rate of 6 words per minute. In 5 minutes, he would be able to type:

6 words/minute * 5 minutes = 30 words

The difference between the number of words he could type in 5 minutes before and after he broke his arm is:

45 words - 30 words = 15 words
